Today  learned how to use the grep command in Linux,which is used to search for specific words or patterns inside files and command outputs.
## Key concepts covered:
-using grep to search for specific text inside a file.
-performing case-insensitive searches using grep -i
-DIsplaying line numbers os matching results using grep -n
-counting how many lines match a pattern using grep -c
-filtering command output using pipes(|) with grep.
